repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
I was able to cross compile onnxruntime for android using  steps provided in [https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/labels/enhancement](BUILD.MD) I have also read #271. However I am still lost on how to use it. The following is the steps I took to cross compile for android:

1- `git clone --recursive https://github.com/Microsoft/onnxruntime`
2- `cd onnxruntime`
3- download android NDK and set `ANDROID_NDK` to point to the unzipped doanloaded file
4- download pre-compiled `protoc` and set `PROTOC_ANDROID` to point to binary protoc
5- while in `onnxruntime` directory, 'cd cmake'
6- `cmake -CMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=$ANDROID_NDK/build/cmake/android.toolchain.cmake -DANDROID_ABI=arm64-v8a -DONNX_CUSTOM_PROTOC_EXECUTABLE=PROTOC_ANDROID`
7- After cmake successful execution, run `make` to build (takes ~20min)

I successfully completed all these steps but I don't know whats output to all of this? how can I use it in my app?

**System information**
- I used latest code on onnxruntime github repo
- I am using ubuntu 16LTS

It is an initial PR for Android NNAPI execution provider. Currently the `GetSupportedNodes` returns the whole model if the model is supported or an empty vector if the model is unsupported. It will be improved soon.
